@svendx4f why the mkdir & chmod 777 in the travis conf? the mkdir is already covered in run_tests and the chmod seems not required and a workaround for something.

Furthermore, I wondering if it is required to do the tests in separate travis environments as all dependencies are available in every docker container. The amount of builds explodes a bit and is also being cached (ie every build caches around 1GB at the moment).

It is good the test the several backends so thumbs up on that one!
